# Alcohol Withdrawal Triage & Complications Model v2.0

Production-grade multi-class model for TriageGeist hackathon predicting ESI triage acuity (1-5), built on Kiza's v10.14 SOTA stacking architecture.

## Key Discovery: TriageGeist Already Has Data

> [!IMPORTANT]
> TriageGeist provides **real competition data** (80k train / 20k test). The target is `triage_acuity` (1-5). The competition says "no provided dataset" in NOTE.md but the CSV files are real structured data. Our primary goal is to **maximize competition score** using this data, while incorporating alcohol/withdrawal domain expertise as feature engineering enrichment.

**Data overview:**
- [train.csv](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/train.csv) — 80k rows, 40 columns (vitals, demographics, arrival info, `triage_acuity` target)
- [test.csv](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/test.csv) — 20k rows (same features, no target)
- `chief_complaints.csv` — 100k rows (free-text `chief_complaint_raw`, system category)
- `patient_history.csv` — 100k rows (25 binary history flags: `hx_liver_disease`, `hx_substance_use_disorder`, etc.)
- [sample_submission.csv](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/sample_submission.csv) — patient_id + triage_acuity (integer 1-5)
- **Class distribution:** ESI-1 (3222), ESI-2 (13439), ESI-3 (28921), ESI-4 (23020), ESI-5 (11398)

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> **Dual model strategy**: The plan builds (A) the **competition pipeline** for TriageGeist leaderboard score, and (B) the **alcohol-specific supplementary model** for withdrawal severity & complications as a showcase. Both share architecture from v10.14.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Text features**: chief_complaints have rich free text. We'll use TF-IDF + truncated SVD for Kaggle compatibility. ClinicalBERT is optional and heavy — recommend skipping for the initial submission.

